  "text": "HR, systolic and diastolic blood pressure, and BIS were extracted from the files and the mean (SD) values were calculated for the 120 s periods before induction of anaesthesia, before electrical stimulation (after induction of anaesthesia) and before laryngoscopy. The maximal HR, blood pressure and BIS in the 300 s after tracheal intubation were determined. An increase in systolic arterial pressure of >20 mm Hg and/or maximal HR after intubation more than 90 were defined as a response to tracheal intubation. [CITATION_1] The recorded signals from the periods before (60 s before tetanic stimulus) and after the stimulus (60 s after the onset of tetanic stimulus) were analysed off-line. The PPG parameters for these periods were computed as described below.",
